properties.name: Appointment Number
properties.title: Appointment Number
properties.description: Unique identifier for appointments in WM

properties.name: Appointment Type Code
properties.title: Appointment Type Code
properties.description:
This field identified the purpose of the appointment. Possible values are :
- Live Unload -The trailer is unloaded but the tractor is still attached.
- Drop Unload - The loaded trailer is dropped in the yard. The loaded trailer will be moved to the correct dock for unloading at a later point in time.
- Live Load - The trailer is loaded but the tractor is still attached.
- Pickup Load - An empty trailer was loaded at the dock. The driver arrives at a later point in time to pick up the loaded trailer.
- Pickup Empty - The driver has come to pick up an empty trailer.
- Drop Empty - The driver has come to drop off an empty trailer.

properties.name: Appointment Status Code
properties.title: Appointment Status Code
properties.description:
This field represent the current state of the appointment. Possible values are :
- 1000 - Requested
- 2000 - Countered
- 3000 - Scheduled
- 4000 - Checked_In
- 8000 - Complete
- 9000 - Cancelled

properties.name: Inbound Delivery Number
properties.title: Inbound Delivery Number
properties.description:
For inbound appointments the shipment number represent the Inbound Delivery carrying products from multiple vendors to the warehouse. One or multiple ASN can be assigned to an Inbound Delivery. One or multiple Inbound Deliveries can be assigned to an appointment

For outbound appointments the shipment number represents a shipment carrying cartons for multiple customers from the warehouse. One or multiple outbound shipments can be assigned to an appointment
